Pick the sites Google likes. That way, your name has a better chance of coming back in the top first page returns when people search online for you and your talents. Google is always reworking its algorithms, so check Alexa and similar to find out which social networking sites are currently hip and happening. Link to high page rank sites that are related to your site is the key. Submit to directories such as Add Your Site Free Submit{"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/Get-Popular-on-the-Internet-Step-8.jpg/v4-460px-Get-Popular-on-the-Internet-Step-8.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/b/bf/Get-Popular-on-the-Internet-Step-8.jpg/v4-760px-Get-Popular-on-the-Internet-Step-8.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":284,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":469.7802197802198,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
